dly chatted about nothing in particular, laughed at gnomes(has this changed??), got wasted by a bixie and basically had a laugh.  <br>
<br>
I remember a time whether you were in a guild or not you were part of a community, this community called Quellious.  Guild tag or not you were there to help one another.  I spent the best part of 52 levels unguilded, so rather than just focussing on my own, I focus on helping anyone.  <br>
<br>
People I have helped in the past include members of LC, they include members of Wraith, they include members of VM, RiP, ADD filtering right down to the non-guilded players.  <br>
<br>
I, like then still offer those services today ... I still help newbies ... I answer their questions, if they are getting trained, I try and stop them from dying best that I can. <br>
<br>
Guilds were nice back then, very outward and flexible thinking.  <br>
<br>
Nowadays, guilds specifically (and guilds I have been involved in) actually have no form of etiquette whatsoever.  They just say &quot;Your not in my guild you can piss off&quot; form of attitude.<br>
<br>
I find this attitude absolutely disgraceful,  guilds have turned from being welcoming people to inward thinking, selfish and unreasonable assholes.  <br>
<br>
Forgive my bluntness for this, but this is the way I see it.  <br>
<br>
I dont care for loot, I dont do camp stealing, I dont do KSing and I definitely dont do ninja looting.  Never have, never will.....I would rather do without. <br>
<br>
Yes, I have decent equipment but this has all been done what I consider to be the right way, through grit, determination, commitment, networking and patience.<br>
<br>
This is not a post to measure @#%$ sizes, this is a post about people's attitudes to EQ and Quellious in general.  <br>
